 preferable to a more principle-driven president, whether Democrat or Republican.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Trump is a businessman. We can just pay him money and the problems will be solved,&rdquo; said a politically connected person in Beijing, speaking on the condition of anonymity to talk frankly about sensitive international issues. <strong>&ldquo;As long as we have money, we can buy him. That&rsquo;s the reason why we prefer him to Democrats.&rdquo;</strong><br />\n.....<br />\n&ldquo;Trump isn&rsquo;t ideologically opposed to China. He doesn&rsquo;t go on about human rights and Xinjiang and the South China Sea,&rdquo; the Beijing insider said, referring to China&rsquo;s contested maritime claims and to its northwestern region where authorities have detained a million Muslims."},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-26T19:34:32.000Z","msg":"同上屆論調一九様"}]}